    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-11T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-11T15:00:00-05:00" n="945"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d945">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.6363/563: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-11T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 11, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>463. Confirmation has been obtained of suspicions expressed in Embassy’s A–920,
                    April 29,<note n="76" xml:id="d945fn76">Not printed.</note> that chief purpose
                    of trip of heads of local oil companies to the United States is to obtain
                    additional grant of gas oil for Cuba. Apparently a deal has been made whereby
                    ORPA granted increase in local sales price of gas oil in exchange for oil
                    company agitation in Washington in favor of additional essential quota gas oil
                    for Cuba. Embassy urges gentlemen’s agreement provided no extra allotment be
                    granted. Further details will be forwarded by airgram today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
